The paper discusses the synthesis of robot controller software using artificial evolution, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Artificial Homeostatic Hormone Systems (AHHS) involves the application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The investigation of how the design of the controller and hormone network size affects evolvability involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
